        "text": " or of a ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "play upon logic",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " is not to be thought of, although Delitzsch himself maintains that something of the kind is possible. Among the unwarrantable and evasive interpretations of certain expositors is that of Paulus, who thinks that the object of the question of Jesus from beginning to end was the ",
        "children": []
