  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Expositor's Greek Testament",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Matthew 22:43",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "πῶς οὖν",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", etc.: the question is meant to bring out another side of Messiah’s relation to David, based on an admittedly Messianic oracle (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Psalm 110:1",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "), and overlooked by the scribes. The object of the question is not, as some have supposed, to deny ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "in toto",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " the sonship, but to hint doubt as to the ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "importance",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " attached to it. Think out the idea of Lordship and see where it will lead you, said Jesus in effect. The scribes began at the wrong end: at the physical and material, and it landed them in secularity. If they had begun with Lordship it would have led them into the spiritual sphere, and made them ready to accept as Christ one greater than David in the spiritual order, though totally lacking the conventional grandeur of royal persons, only an unpretending Son of ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Man",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ".",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
